The "King Salman World Blitz & Rapid Championships 2017" in Riyadh from December 26th to 30th. The first five rounds of the rapid tournament take place on December 26th. A record $2 million prize fund has attracted most of the world's best players.

Sergey Karjakin vs Andrey Esipenko
World Rapid Championship (2017), Riyadh KSA, rd 9, Dec-29 
Nimzowitsch-Larsen Attack: Modern Variation (A01)

1. b3 e5 2. Bb2 Nc6 3. e3 Nf6 4. Bb5 Bd6 5. Na3 e4 6. Nc4 Be7 7. Bxc6 dxc6 8. Ne2 O-O 9. O-O c5 10. Ng3 Re8 11. f3 exf3 12. Qxf3 Rf8 13. e4 Bg4 14. Qf2 Be6 15. d3 Ng4 16. Qf3 b5 17. Na5 Bf6 18. Bxf6 Nxf6 19. a4 a6 20. Qe3 Nd7 21. Nc6 Qh4 22. Nf5 Bxf5 23. Rxf5 Rae8 24. Rd5 Qg4 25. Qg3 Qe6 26. Qxc7 Nf6 27. Rxc5 Kh8 28. Nd4 Qg4 29. Nf3 Rc8 30. Qd6 Rxc5 31. Qxf8+
